Limitations
===========

You may NOT use the Software for a Competing Use.

A "Competing Use" means making the Software available to others as a managed 
service, a software-as-a-service (SaaS), a service bureau, or as part of an 
application services provider (ASP) offering that is competitive with the 
Software. For clarity, a Competing Use specifically includes:

- Offering the Software's API testing, discovery, or development capabilities as 
  a service to third parties
- Providing a hosted or managed version of the Software
- Offering a service that substantially replicates the Software's core functionality

You may use the Software for a Competing Use if ALL of the following conditions 
are met:

(a) You are either:
    - An individual person using the Software for personal, non-commercial purposes
    - A non-profit organization, educational institution, or open source project

(b) You do not offer the Software as a multi-tenant service

Internal business use (using the Software to test your own APIs within your 
organization) is expressly permitted and is NOT considered a Competing Use, 
regardless of your company size or revenue.

